SIMPLE: wince
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wince
<hw>Wince</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Winced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Wincing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wincen</ets>, <ets>winchen</ets>, OF. <ets>quencir</ets>,
<ets>guenchir</ets>, <ets>guenchier</ets>, <ets>giencier</ets>,
<ets>guinchier</ets>, and (assumed) <ets>winchier</ets>,
<ets>winchir</ets>, to give way, to turn aside, fr. OHG.
<ets>wankjan</ets>, <ets>wenken</ets>, to give way, to waver, fr.
<ets>winchan</ets> to turn aside, to nod, akin to E. <ets>wink</ets>.
See <er>Wink</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To shrink, as from a blow, or from pain; to flinch;
to start back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will not stir, nor <qex>wince</qex>, nor speak a word.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To kick or flounce when unsteady, or impatient at a
rider; <as>as, a horse <ex>winces</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wince</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wince
<hw>Wince</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of one who winces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wince</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wince
<hw>Wince</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Winch</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Dyeing & Calico Printing)</fld> <def>A reel used in dyeing,
steeping, or washing cloth; a winch. It is placed over the division wall
between two wince pits so as to allow the cloth to descend into either
compartment. at will.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Wince pit</b></col>, <col><b>Wince
pot</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a tank or a pit where cloth in the process of
dyeing or manufacture is washed, dipped in a mordant, or the
like.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wincer</ent>⟦br⟧
